2024-06-13 15:22:32,951 [system.py:update_program()] - program: {'channel': 'dev', 'debug_enabled': False, 'channel_invalid': False, 'is_valid': True, 'configured_type': 'git_repo', 'info_tags': [], 'detected_type': 'git_repo', 'remote_alias': 'origin', 'branch': 'master', 'owner': 'Klipper3d', 'repo_name': 'klipper', 'remote_url': 'https://github.com/Klipper3d/klipper', 'recovery_url': 'https://github.com/Klipper3d/klipper', 'version': 'v0.12.0-207', 'remote_version': 'v0.12.0-230', 'rollback_version': 'v0.12.0-205', 'current_hash': '6cd174208bd9bbd51dc0d519a26661fb926d038a', 'remote_hash': '0d87bec159eba63744d820b5beaef5da20388ba4', 'is_dirty': False, 'detached': False, 'commits_behind': [{'sha': '0d87bec159eba63744d820b5beaef5da20388ba4', 'author': 'Eric Callahan', 'date': '1718156185', 'subject': 'ci-install: update gnu-pru to version 2024.05', 'message': 'Signed-off-by:  Eric Callahan <arksine.code@gmail.com>', 'tag': None}, {'sha': '589bd64ce013691ef8989d3dfbc74ffe0822d480', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036832', 'subject': 'command: Support 2-byte message ids', 'message': "Allow command ids, response ids, and output ids to be either 1 or 2\nbytes long.  This increases the total number of message types from 128\nto 16384.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '36b8831c7e7c4e4481704234fbc27dbe43026f73', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036832', 'subject': 'sensor_bulk: Change maximum data size from 52 to 51 bytes', 'message': "Reduce the maximum data size from 52 bytes to 51 bytes.  This will\nenable support for 2-byte response ids.\n\nThis change would alter the behavior of the ldc1612 sensor support.\nForce an ldc1612 command name change so that users are alerted that\nthey must rebuild the micro-controller code upon update of the host\ncode.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '17c645f000da6fe99bf75fd79f8e622747b1709e', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036832', 'subject': 'msgproto: Support multi-byte command and response ids', 'message': "Update the msgproto.py code so that it can support message ids that\nare larger than a single byte.  (The host C code in\nklippy/chelper/msgblock.c already supports multi-byte ids.)\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'd4bae4dffe8d3996ed1b1dd8f5230a062ae3d033', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Simplify PrinterProbe() now that there are no external callers', 'message': "Create the mcu_probe interface locally within PrinterProbe().\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '931d1ce8f42ed112e6655c9524367941efb86595', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe_eddy_current: No need to use PrinterProbe() class', 'message': "Directly register the PrinterEddyProbe() class as the main probe\ninterface.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '93245b3678b4bf64b5aff8322d5d5b3de38d00d2', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'smart_effector: No need to use PrinterProbe() class', 'message': "Directly register the SmartEffectorProbe() class as the main probe\ninterface.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '068d2a9f5a70d87dd1158c22c8573e1823ec2fa1', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'bltouch: No need to use PrinterProbe() class', 'message': "Directly register the BLTouchProbe() class as the main probe\ninterface.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'f72f94e299e33c77e6c1a4a75cf632fc8fc812e0', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Move add_steppers() logic to HomingViaProbeHelper class', 'message': "Perform the initial add_steppers() configuration in a single location.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '58753e58a24678b78379d9fa124e691ffd624394', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Use ppins.setup_pin() helper', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'abfe3675d69f11567f7592f4b9659d2db46911a8', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'bltouch: Use ppins.setup_pin() helper', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'e780049a74310d23d110d8beac37b980459893a4', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Use an event for axis twist compensation updates', 'message': "Instead of directly calling axis_twist_compensation, send an event\nthat can perform the necessary updates.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'f4adb2999920e203445e0d6e12b0b08650ae5e19', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Ensure all external callers always call end_probe_session()', 'message': "Rework ProbeSessionHelper's multi_probe_start() and multi_probe_end()\nto start_probe_session() and end_probe_session().  Ensure all external\ncallers always invoke these methods prior to running run_probe().\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '982a50c70ae6aa17538806de41137158ef682d58', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Split z_virtual_endstop handling to new HomingViaProbeHelper class', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'de9798fb5be252627a47d73b89607243e201cab6', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Move offset handling to new ProbeOffsetsHelper class', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'f9a2920cee3b9311788bb5c53f1a9b4a3a01c9ee', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Move PROBE_ACCURACY command to ProbeCommandHelper class', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '292512f8136ffabbc500612f1c80bdbe2588b8e1', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Move PROBE_CALIBRATE to ProbeCommandHelper class', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '6ea5b94d1e3add2bb15cbe9c2f5fd9c7da2e0970', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Convert probe.get_lift_speed() to probe.get_print_params()', 'message': "Add a get_print_params() method that can extract all the common\nprobing parameters.  Replace get_lift_speed() with this more general\nfunction.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '6f6122a576c42852ca8835f9cef5993d2ac76a1d', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Move Z_OFFSET_APPLY_PROBE to ProbeCommandHelper class', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '8fc11b4a2e0dd33cd99e4d3c8ce4107acf4772ff', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Introduce new ProbeCommandHelper class', 'message': "Move the PROBE and QUERY_PROBE commands from ProbeSessionHelper class\nto new ProbeCommandHelper class.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'bec47e049278e9745173ebdb8b184ff3cf4d98c2', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Split out new ProbeSessionHelper() class from PrinterProbe()', 'message': "Separate out the PrinterProbe() class to make the external probe\ninterfaces more clear.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '12f92c55f1c956bf415b379828c7b0bafae35026', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1718036421', 'subject': 'probe: Code movement in probe.py', 'message': "Move code around in probe.py and add some comments.  No code changes.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '49c0ad63