alias': 'origin', 'branch': 'master', 'owner': 'Klipper3d', 'repo_name': 'klipper', 'remote_url': 'https://github.com/Klipper3d/klipper', 'recovery_url': 'https://github.com/Klipper3d/klipper', 'version': 'v0.12.0-451', 'remote_version': 'v0.13.0-51', 'rollback_version': 'v0.12.0-404', 'current_hash': '730e5951bc453d7c08b9b2a066479f2c0cd25842', 'remote_hash': 'bfda326c2403bf96ff909140dcaf26509476fb3c', 'is_dirty': False, 'detached': False, 'commits_behind': [{'sha': 'bfda326c2403bf96ff909140dcaf26509476fb3c', 'author': 'Timofey Titovets', 'date': '1745163564', 'subject': 'spi_flash: fix spi bus switch (#6906)', 'message': 'Fixes abc76ee963d4154dce0bd56f2fdb946d5065cc86.\n\nSigned-off-by: Timofey Titovets <nefelim4ag@gmail.com>', 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'f2b27d17b78c138e09a7997730c22e19dd6d8476', 'author': 'Russell Cloran', 'date': '1745079175', 'subject': 'stm32: Add support for spi6 on stm32f42x chips', 'message': 'Signed-off-by: Russell Cloran <rcloran@gmail.com>', 'tag': None}, {'sha': '5001983d349ef1a1608e2c884888b9040f80ef89', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745078998', 'subject': 'stm32: Fix pll_base on stm32h7 when using a clock other than 25Mhz', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '73e27aee4f579fd3b34ad01ccd5318f18b2a6711', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745078635', 'subject': 'docs: Update benchmarks for stm32h7', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '0d27195fd4fa8a5e7475a9c2d3023925f19f173a', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745077738', 'subject': 'stm32: Add optimized stm32h7_gpio.c', 'message': "Add optimized gpio functions for stm32h7 - caching the ODR register\ncan notably improve the performance of the gpio_out_toggle() code.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '1f5783a25056669a3d158fa0cf05271ef7f3a3fc', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe: Remove ProbeEndstopSessionHelper', 'message': "Have all callers instantiate the individual helper classes directly.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '37952e8686a7d9ece05b846aaa7fab00b22e74f3', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe_eddy_current: Separate probe style commands from homing operations', 'message': "Separate homing operations (as called from probe:z_virtual_endstop)\nfrom the normal probe command handling.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'ab9b9e8584bbcb59682eb5033d0f50eecbedfc2b', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe_eddy_current: Do not support QUERY_PROBE command', 'message': "Report an error if a user issues a QUERY_PROBE command (instead of\nalways returning not-triggered).\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '3fb1191cad9d78dc433c99235d33be2cdbd0bb43', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe: Add a new LookupZSteppers helper class', 'message': "Split code to lookup the Z stepper from HomingViaProbeHelper to new\nLookupZSteppers class.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'f3a1c914a4821211cd5279c9fbdb64345b50694e', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe: Convert probing_move() callback to use regular probe sessions system', 'message': "Use the normal probe_session_start(), run_probe(),\npull_probed_results(), and end_probe_session() API from\nProbeSessionHelper.  This removes the custom probing_move() callback.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'b2e36e5d98c0cbae422fa777e66c99e900cd6169', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe: Change probing_move() to pass a gcmd instead of (pos, speed)', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'ff0ffedd17ed4a5d3b5f410eff1471e67595aa75', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe: Add a new ProbeParameterHelper class', 'message': "Split multi-sample config reading from ProbeSessionHelper to a new\nProbeParameterHelper class.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '1e87d26707961eed5090332d5e8a95e5363a1427', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe: Add a new lookup_minimum_z() helper function', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'f8de9ae080933e2715b639546c539003e1b34894', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe: Add a new ProbeEndstopSessionHelper class', 'message': "Move the HomingViaProbeHelper() instance from ProbeSessionHelper to a\nnew ProbeEndstopSessionHelper class.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '6a87c5e9f56d95b60ed6d7c471bfdc226353c97e', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001514', 'subject': 'probe: Add a default probing_move() function to HomingViaProbeHelper', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'db7a9cf071abcd7c57ec788b906ff96d7b3c41d9', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001143', 'subject': 'manual_stepper: Implement "drip moves" for manual stepper STOP_ON_ENDSTOP', 'message': 'Currently, `MANUAL_STEPPER STOP_ON_ENDSTOP=1` type commands will move\nuntil hitting the endstop, but it will still always consume the total\namount of move time.  That is, following moves can\'t be started until\nthe total possible time of the homing move is completed.\n\nImplement "drip moves" so that the code only schedules the movement in\nsmall segments.  This allows following movements to be scheduled\nwithout a significant delay.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O\'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>', 'tag': None}, {'sha': '765de72f9e2c390ffc1b637be9cb767f6452b401', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001143', 'subject': 'toolhead: Avoid toolhead.move() and toolhead._process_moves() in drip_move()', 'message': "Implement move checking and trapq loading directly from drip_move().\nThis simplifies the interactions between these components.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '6202a0f3bcf98b839f188a49609a49570b8340d2', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1745001143', 'subject': 'toolhead: Avoid LookAheadQueue calling back into toolhead class', 'message': "Avoid lookahead.flush() calling back into toolhead._process_moves().\nInstead, rename toolhead._process_moves() to\ntoolhead._process_lookahead(), have it call lookahead.flush(), and\nconsistently use it when flushing the lookahead queue.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '413ff19ea8e0e5e09c0233225ffa8ad07b1233d6', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744909582', 'subject': 'neopixel: Add comments on timing', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '4e7fcc27040da2ae72bf44b445a97bf9a981dd98', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744906159', 'subject': 'check-software-div: Add a new build check for software divide', 'message': "Update the build checks to include a check for unexpected software\ndivide operations.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '871637d3f2362ce839f3018040eda670f6a10dd9', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744906159', 'subject': 'Kconfig: Note which chips require software divide operations', 'message': "Add a new HAVE_SOFTWARE_DIVIDE_REQUIRED that indicates which chips\nrequire software divide.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '0fbcc156c5ec30b5f8a2bac3ee5e4ca9a635ab69', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744906159', 'subject': 'neopixel: Make sure nsecs_to_ticks() is always inlined', 'message': "It is a compile-time calculation that needs to be inlined to work.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '56d3f4e64cd258560f090ca7c72b41ba8021cc0a', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744906159', 'subject': 'lcd_st7920: Make sure nsecs_to_ticks() is always inlined', 'message': "It is a compile-time calculation that needs to be inlined to work.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'cb6828ec34496e2ee59cc4e43a64a6b41c59acdc', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744906159', 'subject': 'lcd_hd44780: Make sure nsecs_to_ticks() is always inlined', 'message': "It is a compile-time calculation that needs to be inlined to work.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '3656006a3053e8ec4ac548ac52ded62108dc3a25', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744906064', 'subject': 'stm32: Change hard_pwm.c MAX_PWM to 257', 'message': "Choose a value for MAX_PWM that avoids an expensive run-time division.\n\nSigned-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '7a9b06ad867259f48ec0393701b8c9963c5a6610', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744906064', 'subject': 'stm32: Fix prescaler overflow check in hard_pwm.c', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'acd96047de62077e2ec175c2181317fca79f18ac', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744905265', 'subject': 'docs: Update Config_Changes.md to note software spi is now rate limited', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': None}, {'sha': '516ef1d3616acd7ddfd61b80b562f58a7800ceed', 'author': 'Russell Cloran', 'date': '1744904666', 'subject': 'hall_filament_width_sensor: Add filament switch values to status', 'message': '`hall_filament_width_sensor` contains a runout sensor object internally.\nThis exposes those values in the API status result.\n\n```\nSEND: {"id":123,"method":"objects/query","params":{"objects":{"hall_filament_width_sensor":["enabled","filament_detected","is_active","Diameter","Raw"]}}}\nGOT: b\'{"id":123,"result":{"eventtime":199567.823596603,"status":{"hall_filament_width_sensor":{"enabled":true,"filament_detected":true,"is_active":true,"Diameter":1.9499999999999986,"Raw":6113}}}}\'\n```\n\nThe duplication of `is_active` and `enabled` seems confusing, but both\nof these can be independently manipulated by GCode:\n\n```\nSEND: {"id":123,"method":"gcode/script","params":{"script":"DISABLE_FILAMENT_WIDTH_SENSOR"}}\nGOT: b\'{"id":123,"result":{}}\'\nSEND: {"id":123,"method":"objects/query","params":{"objects":{"hall_filament_width_sensor":["enabled","is_active"]}}}\nGOT: b\'{"id":123,"result":{"eventtime":199770.446013297,"status":{"hall_filament_width_sensor":{"enabled":true,"is_active":false}}}}\'\n\nSEND: {"id":123,"method":"gcode/script","params":{"script":"SET_FILAMENT_SENSOR SENSOR=hall_filament_width_sensor ENABLE=0"}}\nGOT: b\'{"id":123,"result":{}}\'\nSEND: {"id":123,"method":"objects/query","params":{"objects":{"hall_filament_width_sensor":["enabled","is_active"]}}}\nGOT: b\'{"id":123,"result":{"eventtime":199847.927726196,"status":{"hall_filament_width_sensor":{"enabled":false,"is_active":false}}}}\'\n```\n\nSigned-off-by: Russell Cloran <rcloran@gmail.com>', 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'b9757c9b69f4c4ec6da7eeb8318235fb1a01f40b', 'author': 'Timofey Titovets', 'date': '1744904564', 'subject': 'tmc: add missing freewheel config options', 'message': 'Signed-off-by: Timofey Titovets <nefelim4ag@gmail.com>', 'tag': None}, {'sha': 'a9b04e853610c216e8ca9db2949e8b658ed67439', 'author': 'Timofey Titovets', 'date': '1744904509', 'subject': 'i2c_software: pass pulse ticks from host', 'message': 'Signed-off-by: Timofey Titovets <nefelim4ag@gmail.com>', 'tag': None}, {'sha': '61c0c8d2ef40340781835dd53fb04cc7a454e37a', 'author': "Kevin O'Connor", 'date': '1744420048', 'subject': 'docs: Note the release of v0.13.0', 'message': "Signed-off-by: Kevin O'Connor <kevin@koconnor.net>", 'tag': 'v0.13.0'}], 'commits_behind_count': 93, 'git_messages': [], 'full_version_string': 'v0.12.0-451-g730e5951